  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the scholarships an MBBS student in India?",
  "response": "MBBS students in India have access to a variety of scholarships provided by the government, private organizations, colleges, and universities. Some of the prominent scholarships for MBBS students in India include:\n\n1. **Government Scholarships:**\n   - **National Talent Search Examination (NTSE) Scholarship:** Provided by the NCERT for students after clearing the NTSE exam.\n   - **Central Sector Scheme of Scholarships for College and University Students:** Provided by the Ministry of Education to undergraduate students, including MBBS students.\n   - **Post Matric Scholarship for Minorities:** Provided by the Ministry of Minority Affairs for minority students.\n   - **Post Matric Scholarship for SC/ST/OBC Students:** Provided by respective central and state governments for students belonging to SC/ST/OBC categories.\n   - **Prime Minister's Scholarship Scheme (PMSS):** Provided for students from the armed forces background.\n\n2. **State Government Scholarships:**\n   - Various state governments provide scholarships for meritorious and underprivileged students based on different criteria. For instance, the Maharashtra State Government Scholarship for Professional Courses.\n\n3. **University/College Scholarships:**\n   - **AIIMS Scholarship:** All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS) and other reputed medical institutions like JIPMER, PGIMER, and Maulana Azad Medical College offer scholarships to meritorious students.\n   - **Institution-specific Scholarships:** Many medical colleges provide scholarships for needy and exceptional students.\n\n4. **Private Scholarships:**\n   - **Tata Trusts Medical and Healthcare Scholarships:** Provided by Tata Trusts for medical students.\n   - **Sitaram Jindal Foundation Scholarship:** Provided by the Sitaram Jindal Foundation for students enrolled in professional courses.\n   - **Indian Oil Academic Scholarships:** Provided by Indian Oil Corporation Limited for meritorious students entering professional courses.\n\n5. **NGO/Foundation Scholarships:**\n   - **MESCO (Muslim Education Society) Scholarship:** Provided to Muslim students for pursuing various professional courses, including MBBS.\n   - **Dr. Shamanur Shivashankarappa Scholarship for Medical & Engineering Students:** Provided to meritorious students pursuing MBBS.\n\nStudents are encouraged to regularly check for such scholarships, read the eligibility criteria, and complete the application process within the stipulated time frames.",
